name: nim-rag-blueprint
description: The NVIDIA blueprint for the RAG pipeline utilizes Dataloop's AI Playground to enable efficient interaction with models. It leverages NIM models for generating embeddings and responses, and incorporates a retriever service to effectively fetch relevant documents from the source dataset. The model's responses are stored in the prompts dataset and subsequently sent to a labeling task, enabling human-in-the-loop validation and refinement.

variables.name: embed_model
variables.description: Embedding model, used for embedding the user prompt questions.

variables.name: gen_ai_model
variables.description: Generative model that generate the response.

variables.name: retrieval_embed_model
variables.description: Embedding model, that was used for embedding the retrival dataset items.

variables.name: k_nearest_items
variables.description: K nearest items - The number of closest items to retrieve. Default set to 30.
